pr_body:
For faster RSS updates, per social squad

Will also update on 0-7-x branch

@spra85 @benghaziboy @MichaelButkovic

This PR eliminates simplereduce handler and its subclasses, and fixes the cases in the main code that those handlers were papering over. 

This also catches a few undocumented edgecases with reduce behaviour, and some under-explored cases, like proxies interacting with reduce.

@davvid

Fixes #14.

The `flush()` is necessary because of the following scenario:
 - write exceeds fs capacity but isn't flushed, write call doesn't fail, file is at position beyond fs capacity;
 - next call writes enough to flush;
 - next call fails but going back to previous position still exceeds fs capacity;

It could however become a performance issue. Could be fixed by a file object that keeps a buffer in memory by itself and only calls write in KB-sized blocks.

Integration https://github.com/Blosc/bcolz/pull/72 #132 and some leftovers' api tests
